data.content:
Here are the breaking changes for each snippet in .NET 10:

---

### 1. `Form1.cs` — Ambiguous types (build error)

Since you have both `<UseWPF>` and `<UseWindowsForms>`, `MenuItem` and `ContextMenu` are now ambiguous between `System.Windows.Forms` and `System.Windows.Controls`. Fully qualify them:

```csharp
var menu = new System.Windows.Forms.ContextMenu();
menu.MenuItems.Add(new System.Windows.Forms.MenuItem("Open", OnOpen));
```

### 2. `ImageProcessor.cs` — Exception type changed (behavioral)

`System.Drawing` operations that threw `OutOfMemoryException` now throw `ExternalException`. Your `catch` will silently miss errors:

```csharp
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

try
{
    using var bmp = new Bitmap(path);
    bmp.SetResolution(300, 300);
}
catch (ExternalException ex)     // .NET 10+
{
    logger.LogError(ex, "Invalid image format");
}
catch (OutOfMemoryException ex)  // fallback for older runtimes
{
    logger.LogError(ex, "Invalid image format");
}
```

### 3. `MainWindow.xaml` — Two issues (both crash/error)

- **Empty `ColumnDefinitions`/`RowDefinitions`** now cause errors. Remove them.
- **`DynamicResource MissingKey`** referencing a non-existent resource now **crashes** at runtime (previously silently ignored).

```xml
<Grid>
    <!-- Removed empty ColumnDefinitions/RowDefinitions -->
    <TextBlock Text="{DynamicResource MissingKey}" />
    <!-- ↑ Ensure "MissingKey" exists in a ResourceDictionary, or remove/replace it -->
</Grid>
```

### Also mentioned: behavioral changes

- **StatusStrip**: Now uses system render mode. Set `RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.Professional` explicitly to keep the old look.
- **TreeView checkboxes**: Rendering adjusted — text positioning may shift slightly. Visual-only; no code fix needed unless pixel-perfect layout is required.
